rule Bypass_Sample {
    meta:
        description = "Evasion bypass for exit processes in malware analysis"
        cape_options = "bp0=$pattern0+0,action0=skip,bp1=$pattern1+0,action1=skip,bp2=$pattern2+0,action2=skip,count=0"

    strings:
        $pattern0 = { 85 C0 0F 84 ?? ?? ?? ?? 8B 45 ?? }  // Represents a potential initial instruction or address
        $pattern1 = { 6A ?? 5A 8B CE E8 ?? ?? ?? ?? 85 C0 }  // Represents another bypass sequence
        $pattern2 = { C1 E8 E8 ?? ?? ?? ?? ?? ?? ?? 85 C0 }  // Another potential bypass pattern

    condition:
        any()  # Applies to any of the defined patterns
}
